pull_request.title: "Better" teleport validation system.
pull_request.body:
Changes:
- Only accept teleport position if the player have HANDLE_TELEPORT in their input data.
- Some small changes to the ground calculation in BedrockMovePlayer.
- Cleanup some stuff in CollisionManager.
- Compare player floating point position with the actual position we send through MovePlayerPacket instead of using the java double position.
- Instead of not caching the teleport if the distance is small enough, it simply doesn't translate it.
